    "created_at": "2013-10-15T18:43:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-10-15T18:43:13Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm -0 on this change. Not sure why we'd want to have `brief_sys_info` that's used in exactly one place. `sys_info` is exposed at the top-level, i.e.\n\n``` python\nimport IPython\nprint IPython.sys_info()\n```\n\n and I presume that part of the reason it's a dictionary is to make it JSON friendly for sending over the wire for notebook javascript consumption.\n\nI would just take out the `brief_sys_info` function, and have the `report` function in `iptestcontroller.py` do the equivalent to the output of `sys_info`. If, however, you want to keep the extra function, I'd call it `sys_info_brief`, for tab-completion discover-ability.\n\nHaving two functions that do essentially the same thing, but in different ways, will mean having to always update two lines of code, should we decide to add something to `pkg_info`: the `pkg_info` code, and now the `brief_sys_info` code, which only grabs a portion of the pkg_info dictionary right now.\n\nI'm also suspicious of yet-more home directory collapsing logic sprinkled about our codebase: in utils/path.py we need to get the `os.path.realpath(homedir)` for things to work on FreeBSD, for example.\n"
  },
